args:
Phantom sustains a severe wound as a result
of Thanatos's dying attack, but Felicia's love
brings a miraculous revival. Back at the
Halidom, the party promises to reunite with
the pair soon. To celebrate, Felicia dances
in the light.
Me...? Die...? Of all the fool...
No... No! I will not do this!\nI WILL NOT DIE ALONE!
If I am to meet my end here,\nyou will join me in the next world!
We're not gonna make it in ti—
To your last breath, dragon...you insist\non interfering with my designs...
Looks like we made it outta that\nchump's skeezy realm.
Perhaps that means Thanatos has been\ndestroyed for true—but what about Felicia\nand Phantom?
It's no good—the black mana is too\npowerful for my healing magic.
I'm glad...you are all right...\nBut what...of the fiend?
From now on, I hope you live in\nhappiness...in the light...
I will—and you're going to live with me.\nLet's do it together, okay?
I can hardly believe you'd say\nsomething like that...to me.
However...it is an impossible dream.\nThe black mana gnaws at my life...
Sealed away by humans in the space\nbetween worlds, then falling victim\nto this foul black mana...
It looks as though I have finally\nreached my limits.
Felicia... I have a final wish for you...
While I can still see...please dance for me.\nDance in the light.
No, you can't be gone! Phantom!
It takes a real jerk to make a poor\nwoman cry like this.
Aren't you going to protect Felicia?!\nIsn't she important to you?!
If the two of you don't live together,\nthen everything that came before\nwas just meaningless words!
(My life was one of being feared...)
(I was scorned, named fiend, and sealed\naway. Perhaps I ought to have died then.)
(Hmm? What is this? Cold, and yet warm.\n...Is this a tear?)
The black mana is getting weaker...\nI might be able to heal him now!
You have my thanks, sylvan.\nI am saved, thanks to you.
That makes us even for you saving\nme from that curse.
But I was only able to heal you because\nthe black mana weakened.
How did you manage to stave it off,\nPhantom?
Your guess is as good as mine. All I know\nis that I could sense Felicia weeping.
I wanted to stop her crying, and so\nknew I could not remain as I was.
Perhaps it was your desire to live for\nFelicia that purified the black mana.
You may be right, at that.
I'd thought my time on this world had\nalready lasted too long, and yet...
Heh. To think that a day would come\nwhere I would WANT to live.
You're just a little dragon troublemaker,\naren't you?
I was REALLY worried about you,\nand it ended up being for no reason.
I'm just glad it all worked out\nin the end, big fella.
We're all glad—but what are the\ntwo of you gonna do now?
I do not know. With my village\nin its current state...
If the two of you have no place to go,\nyou're welcome to stay with us.
Put me down in the ＂come stay with us＂\ncolumn! Whaddaya say, Felicia?
I truly am delighted by the offer, but...
Go, Felicia. Would you not be relieved to\nonce again have a place to call home?
I do not think it likely I could come.
You may have healed my wounds,\nbut I will need time yet before I am\nable to move unhindered once again.
Then we'll just wait for you to get better.
Have you not matters of your own\nthat need attending to?
Surely you do—and thus I implore you\nto take Felicia and go.
I am most grateful for your invitation,\n{player_name}.
But I am going to stay with Phantom.
I said I wanted to live with you, didn't I?
You saved me from a world of despair\nand darkness.
I could never leave you now.
Oh, for the love of...\nTake the hint already, idiot!
My darling invited you to come, too!
So once you can move again,\nthe two of you just come TOGETHER!
Mym's right. We'll be waiting for you,\nso show up anytime.
You are a truly easy-going prince.\n...But very well.
When I have regained my strength,\nI shall hasten to your castle.
We'll all be looking forward to that day.
Felicia, are you truly certain you do not\nmind staying here?
Of course not. I'm going to take care of\nyou until you're able to move once more.
In that case...might I see you dance\nonce more?
